pageContext.description: This appears to have been intended for the chase and not for warfare, as similar ones are generally found in old hunting grounds. 2 holes which are practically filled with encrusted metal.
pageContext.surface: Smooth. Bronze coloured shades from golden to reddish and dark brown. Very tiny pits all over.
pageContext.other: Width: blade 35mm; socket 22.5mm,Thickness: socket 22mm; blade 14.5mm,Weight: 120.47 gms
pageContext.collection: Society of Antiquaries,B.23,Burlington House W,Dr. Roots' Collection, No. 10
pageContext.site: England, middlesex,close to thames at hampton,near bushy park,1855
